# Component Patterns

## Hero Section Structure

The hero follows a consistent vertical flow:

```tsx
function Hero() {
  return (
    <header className={styles.hero}>
      {/* 1. Avatar */}
      <Image
        src="/avatar.jpg"
        alt="Your Name"
        width={60}
        height={60}
        className={styles.avatar}
        draggable={false}
      />
      
      {/* 2. Name */}
      <h1 className={styles.name}>Your Name</h1>
      
      {/* 3. Tagline - same size as name, secondary color */}
      <p className={styles.tagline}>
        Designer at Company, based in City.
      </p>
      
      {/* 4. Social links */}
      <nav className={styles.socialLinks}>
        <SocialLink href="https://x.com/handle" icon={<XIcon />} />
        <SocialLink href="https://github.com/handle" icon={<GitHubIcon />} />
      </nav>
    </header>
  );
}
```

## Link List Pattern

Two-column on desktop, single column on mobile:

```tsx
function ProjectList({ projects }) {
  return (
    <ul className={styles.projectList}>
      {projects.map((project) => (
        <li key={project.slug} className={styles.projectItem}>
          <Link href={project.url} className={styles.projectLink}>
            <span className={styles.projectTitle}>{project.title}</span>
            <span className={styles.projectDescription}>
              {project.description}
            </span>
            {project.external && <ExternalIcon />}
          </Link>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
}
```

## External Link Indicator

Always indicate outbound links:

```tsx
function ExternalLink({ href, children }) {
  return (
    <a 
      href={href}
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      className={styles.externalLink}
    >
      {children}
      <svg 
        width={16} 
        height={16} 
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <path 
          stroke="currentColor" 
          strokeWidth={1.5}
          strokeLinecap="round"
          strokeLinejoin="round"
          d="M17.25 15.25V6.75H8.75M17 7L6.75 17.25"
        />
      </svg>
    </a>
  );
}
```

## Video Thumbnail Card

For project showcases with motion:

```tsx
function ProjectCard({ project }) {
  return (
    <Link href={project.url} className={styles.projectCard}>
      <div className={styles.thumbnail}>
        <video
          autoPlay
          muted
          loop
          playsInline
          src={project.videoSrc}
          className={styles.video}
        />
      </div>
    </Link>
  );
}
```

## Semantic HTML Requirements

Always use proper heading hierarchy:

```tsx
// ❌ Bad
<div className="title">Page Title</div>
<div className="section-title">Section</div>

// ✅ Good
<h1>Page Title</h1>
<section>
  <h2>Section</h2>
</section>
```

## Accessibility Patterns

```tsx
// Icon buttons need labels
<button aria-label="Open menu">
  <MenuIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</button>

// Links should be descriptive
<a href="/projects/bloom">
  View Bloom project {/* Not just "Click here" */}
</a>

// Images need alt text
<Image 
  src="/project.jpg" 
  alt="Screenshot of the Bloom menu component"
/>

// Decorative images
<Image 
  src="/pattern.svg" 
  alt="" 
  aria-hidden="true"
/>
```

## Section Component Pattern

Consistent section wrapper:

```tsx
function Section({ title, children }) {
  return (
    <section className={styles.section}>
      {title && (
        <>
          <h2 className={styles.sectionTitle}>{title}</h2>
          <div className={styles.separator} />
        </>
      )}
      {children}
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Avoid These Patterns

```tsx
// ❌ Inline styles
<div style={{ marginTop: 20, color: '#333' }}>

// ❌ Generic div soup
<div className="wrapper">
  <div className="container">
    <div className="content">

// ❌ Non-semantic buttons
<div onClick={handleClick}>Click me</div>

// ✅ Use semantic elements
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
<nav>...</nav>
<main>...</main>
<article>...</article>
```
